<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 9:00AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...SHOWERS WITH GUSTY WINDS WILL AFFECT NORTHERN
PITTSYLVANIA...SOUTHWESTERN BEDFORD...NORTHEASTERN HENRY AND EASTERN
FRANKLIN COUNTIES...
At 858 AM EDT, a band of showers with gusty winds was located over
Sydnorsville, moving northeast at 35 mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph are possible with this shower.
Locations impacted include...
Rocky Mount...
Gretna...
Huddleston...
Sydnorsville...
Moneta...
Penhook...
and Snow Creek.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
